        "description": "When a Contact is marked as Deceased, this handler automatically selects Do Not Contact, Do Not Call, and Email Opt Out, and removes the deceased Contact from the Household Account Name, Formal Greeting, and Informal Greeting fields. If the deceased Contact is the Primary Contact on the Household, NPSP assigns the Household member with the highest giving amount (or earliest creation date as a tiebreaker) as the new Primary Contact. When the last living Contact in a Household is marked deceased, the All Members Deceased checkbox is selected on the Account. Marking a Contact as Do Not Contact without Deceased similarly selects Do Not Call and Email Opt Out. Accidental Deceased flags must be manually reversed on both the Contact and the automatically updated Household fields. The source code This handler runs BeforeInsert and BeforeUpdate on Contact and enforces a hierarchy between the Deceased and Do Not Contact flags: if both change simultaneously, Deceased takes precedence. When a Contact is marked deceased, it calls `markContactDeceased()` which sets `Do_Not_Contact__c = true`, then calls `markContactDoNotContact()` which sets `HasOptedOutOfEmail` and `DoNotCall`, and then calls `excludeFromHHNaming()` which sets all three household naming exclusion flags — all within the same before-trigger context so no additional DML is needed for these field updates. The only DML in this handler is a potential update to the Account's `npe01__One2OneContact__c` to reassign the Primary Contact when the deceased contact was previously primary and there are surviving non-deceased household members; the replacement is chosen as `contacts[0]` from a subquery ordered by `npo02__TotalOppAmount__c DESC, CreatedDate ASC`, meaning NPSP picks the highest donor as the new primary when one is available."
