        "description": "Batch Apex class that handles Campaign Member deduplication at the Household level for Campaigns too large for synchronous processing. It identifies when multiple Contacts from the same Household are members of the same Campaign and appends \" - Household Duplicate\" to the Status of the lower-priority duplicates, so that mailing lists show only one address per Household. This is the asynchronous counterpart to the synchronous Household Mailing List action, and both paths use the same deduplication algorithm to produce consistent results. The source code This batch class accepts an externally constructed SOQL string (passed from `HH_CampaignDedupeBTN_CTRL`) as its query locator, which means the actual record selection logic lives entirely outside this class. Its `execute` method simply delegates to `HH_CampaignDedupeBTN_CTRL.MarkDuplicatesFromList()`, keeping the deduplication algorithm in one place and ensuring batch and synchronous paths produce identical results. The batch size of 2,000 is set at the caller site rather than inside the class, making it straightforward to tune without changing batch internals."
