        "sourceUrl": "https://github.com/SalesforceFoundation/NPSP/blob/main/force-app/main/default/classes/HH_Container_LCTRL.cls",
        "description": "Lightning controller that powers the Manage Household page, providing all the read and write operations for Household Accounts and their member Contacts. It supports the full set of household management tasks: merging Households (adding an individual Contact or importing all members from another Household), splitting Households (removing a Contact to their own new Household), reordering Contact names via drag-and-drop to control the name display sequence, and configuring per-Contact naming exclusions. It coordinates reads and writes across Account, Contact, and Address records, and administrators using this page need Read, Create, Delete, View All Records, and Modify All Records permissions on Accounts, Contacts, and Addresses. The source code This is the largest class in the contacts domain at 950 lines. Its `saveHouseholdPage()` method orchestrates a multi-step save sequence that must execute in a specific order: resolve the current default Address undeliverability status first, update the Household Account record with `TDTM_ProcessControl.setRecursionFlag(TDTM_ProcessControl.flag.HH, true)` to suppress re-entrant naming triggers, merge any losing Household Accounts (via native `merge` DML), upsert all Contacts with a `DMLOptions.duplicateRuleHeader.allowSave = true` override to bypass duplicate warnings, and then clean up Address records. The TDTM bypass flag is critical: without it, saving the Account with the freshly computed name would cause `ACCT_Accounts_TDTM` to detect the name change as a manual override and lock out auto-naming for that Household permanently via `npo02__SYSTEM_CUSTOM_NAMING__c`. The `upsertContacts()` method constructs a defensive copy of each Contact (`new Contact(Id=con.Id)`) and uses `UTIL_Describe.copyObjectFLS()` to copy only the fields the UI declares as editable, preventing mass-assignment of unexpected fields from the Lightning component payload. A `savepoint/rollback` wraps only the Contact DML, not the full save sequence, so a Contact save failure rolls back contacts but leaves the already-committed Household Account update in place — a deliberate choice to avoid the savepoint consuming an additional governor unit across the merge DML. When a Household merge occurs, the controller also evaluates `Sustainer__c` on the winning Account via `RD2_SustainerEvaluationService` to keep the sustainer flag consistent with the merged recurring donation portfolio."
