        "description": "TDTM trigger handler for the legacy Household custom object that handles changes to Household Name, Formal Greeting, and Informal Greeting when a legacy Household record is updated. This handler is only relevant for organizations still using the One-to-One or Individual Bucket account models with the older custom Household object. In the recommended Household Account model, Household naming is managed directly on the Account record by other automation handlers. Setting Household Object Rules to \"No Contacts\" in NPSP Settings > People > Households is recommended to prevent orphaned legacy Household records. The source code This handler exists solely to bridge the legacy `npo02__Household__c` custom object into the TDTM framework. It delegates all logic to the `LegacyHouseholds` service class (BeforeUpdate calls `onBeforeUpdate()`, AfterUpdate calls `onAfterUpdate()`), which handles naming recalculation for the old Household Object model. The class is registered as a TDTM handler on `npo02__Household__c` rather than on Contact or Account, which means it only fires when the legacy object itself changes — not when its member Contacts change. In the recommended Household Account model, this handler is irrelevant and should generate no activity."
