        "description": "Batch Apex class that regenerates Household names, formal greetings, and informal greetings across all Household records, invoked from NPSP Settings > Bulk Data Processes > Refresh Household Names. It queries Household records and their member Contacts and applies the current naming configuration from Household Name Settings. Before running this batch, admins must disable all custom validation rules on the Account object (or the legacy Household object) that check name or greeting fields, as those validation rules can block the batch from saving. The process is irreversible; Salesforce recommends exporting the current Name, Formal Greeting, and Informal Greeting values before running. The source code This batch class accepts an externally built SOQL query string and uses it directly in `Database.getQueryLocator()`, making the query scope fully caller-controlled. Its `execute()` method branches between legacy Household Object mode (querying `npo02__Household__c`) and Household Account mode (querying Account) based on which `HHId__c` values resolve to each object type. The `npo02__SYSTEM_CUSTOM_NAMING__c` sentinel is checked per household before overwriting names: if a Formal or Informal Greeting is non-null but the sentinel does not already mark that field as custom, the batch appends the field name to the sentinel string — treating any pre-existing non-null greeting as a custom override and preserving it from being overwritten by auto-naming. This prevents the batch from clobbering manually entered names even when auto-naming is technically enabled for that Household."
