        "description": "TDTM trigger handler that creates a Household record for a newly inserted Contact, updates the Household name when Contact information changes, and deletes the Household if no Contacts remain. In the recommended Household Account model, the primary account creation work is handled by a separate handler; this handler's main active role is supporting the legacy One-to-One and Individual Bucket account models using the custom Household object. It also coordinates a specific cross-handler flag during Contact insert to prevent redundant Household naming work in the Household Account model. The source code This handler uses an Apex `switch on triggerAction` statement to dispatch Contact lifecycle events across four phases. The BeforeInsert phase sets `TDTM_ProcessControl.flag.HH_isRunningBeforeInsert` to true to suppress a specific recursion path in `ACCT_Accounts_TDTM`, and the AfterInsert phase clears it; this cross-handler flag coordination is necessary because `ACCT_Accounts_TDTM` would otherwise interpret the Account creation triggered by Contact insert as a second pass requiring its own Household naming work. Legacy Household Object processing (for orgs using One-to-One or Individual Bucket models) is gated behind `orgUsesLegacyHouseholds()`, which checks `HouseholdSettings.isAllProcessor() || isAllIndividualsProcessor()`, ensuring the `LegacyHouseholdMembers` service class is never instantiated in Household Account model orgs. The AfterUpdate path unconditionally constructs a `LegacyHouseholdMembers` instance regardless of account model, which means it runs even in Household Account orgs, though the service class internally guards against taking action when no legacy household IDs are present."
