        "description": "Visualforce controller for the Manage Household page that handles Household creation and save operations. It supports both modern Household Accounts and the legacy Household custom object, configuring the new Account with the correct type and associating member Contacts appropriately. Accessing this page requires Visualforce page access to the NPSP Manage Household pages, plus Read, Create, Delete, View All, and Modify All permissions on Accounts, Contacts, and Addresses. The source code This Visualforce controller handles the legacy Manage Household page and distinguishes between Household Account and legacy Household Object mode via `UTIL_Describe.isObjectIdThisType(hhId, 'Account')`. In legacy Household Object mode, it creates a `npo02__Household__c` record and then updates the Contact's `npo02__Household__c` lookup in a second DML operation — two separate commits that are not wrapped in a savepoint, meaning a Contact update failure leaves an orphaned Household Object in the database. When displaying household fields, the controller uses the `npo02__Manage_Household_Custom` FieldSet to drive the editable field list rather than hardcoding it, allowing orgs to add custom fields to the Manage Household page without code changes. The class correctly gates both Create and Update permission checks before each DML call using `UTIL_Permissions.canCreate()` and `UTIL_Permissions.canUpdate()`."
