        "description": "Visualforce extension class that provides the remote action methods powering the interactive Manage Household page UI. It supports finding Contacts to add (remoteAddMember), removing Household members (remoteRemoveMember), configuring naming overrides for individual Contacts (remoteSetNaming), and saving all changes (remoteSave) through JavaScript remoting calls. These remote actions allow staff to search for Contacts, drag Contact cards to reorder name sequence, configure per-Contact naming exclusions, and choose between adding one Contact or merging all members from another Household. The source code This Visualforce extension class provides JavaScript Remoting methods for the classic Manage Household page, including `remoteAddMember`, `remoteRemoveMember`, `remoteSetNaming`, and `remoteSave`, each marked `@RemoteAction`. It acts as a thin delegation layer over `HH_Container_LCTRL` for data operations, keeping business logic in one place while adapting the method signatures for the JavaScript Remoting calling convention. The class is lightweight at 84 lines with no SOQL and no direct DML, functioning purely as an API bridge."
