        "description": "The core record type that stores physical mailing addresses for Household and Organization Accounts. Each Address record belongs to an Account via a master-detail relationship, giving you a full history of all addresses associated with that household or organization rather than a single overwritable field. NPSP uses this object to power default address management (the Default Address checkbox controls which address syncs to the Account and its Contacts), seasonal address switching (start and end month/day fields tell the nightly job when to activate or deactivate the address), address type classification (home, work, or other), undeliverable tracking, and verification status. The Exclude from Updates checkbox lets you lock an individual address so sync operations will not overwrite it. The Pre-Verification Address field preserves the original address text before any verification service modifies it, so you always have a record of what was entered.",
