        "description": "TDTM trigger handler that automatically creates and maintains Affiliation records linking Contacts to Organizations when contacts are associated with accounts, ensuring that the nonprofit's relationship network is always kept in sync. The source code At 749 lines and 7 SOQL queries, this is the most complex TDTM handler in the affiliations domain. It dispatches separately for Contact, Account, and Affiliation object triggers, using three independent `TDTM_ProcessControl` recursion flags (`AFFL_doNotRunForContacts`, `AFFL_hasRunForAffiliations`, `AFFL_hasRunForAccounts`) to prevent re-entrancy across all three object types simultaneously. The core processing builds a combo-key map (`contactId+accountId`) to detect existing affiliations before issuing inserts, avoiding duplicate affiliation creation even when both the Contact and its Primary_Affiliation field change in the same transaction."
