        "description": "The settings panel that displays the NPSP error log under System Tools, showing date, error type, full message, object type, record link, and stack trace for each logged error; errors are only stored here when Error Handling is enabled. Administrators can clear all logged errors directly from this panel. The source code This panel implements `UTIL_iSoqlListViewConsumer`, an interface that provides a reusable list view component with column definitions, SOQL string, and object type — effectively delegating the data-fetching and pagination to the shared `UTIL_SoqlListView_CTRL` component rather than implementing its own query loop. The `clearErrorLog` method issues a bulk delete limited to 10,000 records in a single DML call, which respects governor limits but silently leaves any overflow if the error log exceeds that count."
