        "description": "A standalone health check component that validates Recurring Donation-specific configuration, including whether Enhanced RD is correctly enabled, installment stage mappings, status automation settings, and whether any data migration from legacy to Enhanced RD is still incomplete. It is invoked as part of the main Health Check and can also be run independently. The source code Declared with `inherited sharing`, this class is designed to run under whatever sharing context the caller has, which is appropriate since the health check is an administrative diagnostic and its data access should reflect the calling panel's permissions. The `validateNewInstallmentOpportunity` method is the most unusual pattern here: it performs a live `Database.insert` of a test `Opportunity` record inside a savepoint, then immediately rolls back, to confirm that the configured installment stage and record type are actually valid in the org — a side-effect-free smoke test executed at configuration-check time. The six validation methods each call `validateSupportedPicklistValues` or `validateRequiredPicklistValues` to compare live picklist values against known-required sets for both legacy RD and Enhanced RD configurations."
