        "description": "Abstract base class for batch jobs that need to process very large tables — millions of records — without hitting governor limits, automatically switching to an ID-range-chunked query strategy when the data volume exceeds a configurable threshold. The source code Implements both `Database.Batchable` and `Database.Stateful`, using stateful fields (`startId`, `endId`, `currentEndId`, `chunkIteration`, `ldvMode`) to track pagination state across batch executions. The LDV mode activates automatically when the count of records between `startId` and `endId` exceeds `DEFAULT_MAX_NON_LDV_SIZE` (1,000,000), switching from a standard batch query to ID-range-chunked queries with configurable `getLDVChunkSize()` (default 1,000,000 IDs per chunk). Subclasses must implement `getSObjectType()` and `doExecute()`, and can override `getWhereClause()`, `onStart()`, `doFinish()`, and `getSOQLFullQueryFieldList()` to specialize behavior without reimplementing the chunking logic."
