        "description": "The primary service that orchestrates NPSP feature usage data collection and reporting, gathering metrics on Household Account Model status, Customizable Rollups enablement, Gift Entry status, Enhanced Recurring Donations state, error log volume, batch job timeout counts, trigger handler usage, and record counts — all reported back to Salesforce.org for package intelligence and support. The source code Declared `without sharing` to ensure consistent telemetry counts regardless of the executing user's record visibility. The service wraps advanced multi-currency detection in a try/catch because the `DatedConversionRate` object only exists in orgs with Advanced Currency Management enabled, and querying it in a non-ACM org throws a `QueryException`. It uses `UTIL_FeatureManagement.setPackageBooleanValue()` and `setPackageIntegerValue()` to write telemetry back to the License Management Org via feature parameters, making this class the exclusive channel for all NPSP usage data reporting."
