        "description": "Singleton utility class that checks whether the running user has the required CRUD and field-level security permissions before NPSP performs data operations, ensuring the package respects Salesforce's record and field access controls. The source code Declared `with sharing` and follows a singleton pattern (`getInstance()` / `setInstance()`) so tests can inject a mock permissions checker. The class provides both static and instance method variants for every permission type (canRead, canCreate, canUpdate, canDelete), with an optional `throwException` boolean parameter that converts a `false` result into a thrown `InsufficientPermissionException` rather than returning false, allowing callers to choose between guard-and-throw and check-and-branch patterns."
