        "sourceUrl": "https://github.com/SalesforceFoundation/NPSP/blob/main/force-app/main/default/classes/ALLO_AllocationsWrapper.cls",
        "description": "Central data container that carries all allocation records through the four-step processing pipeline — loading, review, recalculation, and save — eliminating redundant database queries between stages. It organizes allocations by parent type (donations, payments, campaigns, recurring gifts) and provides typed accessor methods for retrieving allocation sets by parent ID, as well as mutation methods for staging the inserts, updates, and deletions that the final save step will commit. This shared structure is what allows each processing stage to hand off work to the next without re-querying the database. The source code This central data container accumulates all allocation changes across four parent object types—Opportunity, Payment, Campaign, and Recurring Donation—using lazy-initialized maps keyed by parent Id, with a parallel `paymentIdsToOppIds` reverse-lookup map that links payment Ids back to their Opportunity. Three separate staging lists (`allocationsForInsert`, `allocationsForUpdate`, `allocationsForDelete`) collect pending DML work, while an `exclusionsByOpportunityId` map carries per-record `processDefinitionType` exclusion sets that survive from the review phase into the DML phase. The class uses 45 Lists and 30 Maps (566 lines) and includes `filterParentAllocations()` logic that trims orphaned entries from parent maps when opportunities are removed from scope mid-transaction."
