        "referencedObjects": [],
        "sourceUrl": "https://github.com/SalesforceFoundation/NPSP/blob/main/force-app/main/default/classes/ALLO_MakeDefaultAllocations_BATCH.cls",
        "description": "One-time setup batch job that creates default GAU Allocation records for all existing donations that do not yet have any allocations, except those excluded via the GAU Allocations Rollup Settings. This is typically run once when an administrator first enables the default allocations feature in NPSP Settings > Donations > GAU Allocations, and it can be triggered on demand from the Bulk Data Processes > Batch Create Default Allocations page. After this job completes, all future unallocated donations will automatically receive a default GAU allocation at the time they are created. The source code This batch class iterates all Opportunities and creates default GAU allocations for any that do not yet have one, applying the same exclusion filters from `Allocations_Settings__c` (excluded record types and types) in its `isExcluded()` check to skip opportunities that should not receive default allocations. It explicitly sets `TDTM_ProcessControl.setRecursionFlag(TDTM_ProcessControl.flag.ALLOC, true)` before its DML and clears it in the `finish()` method, preventing the `ALLO_Allocations_TDTM` handler from re-processing its own inserted allocations and triggering a cascade."
