        "description": "Creates and synchronizes Account Soft Credit records when Contact Roles on donations are created, updated, or deleted. For organizational donations, when a Primary Contact is populated, this handler automatically creates a Soft Credit Contact Role for that Contact, ensuring the Contact's soft credit totals reflect the organizational gift while the Account retains the hard credit. It evaluates non-primary Contact Roles to identify which organizational accounts should receive soft credit. The source code This handler fires on `OpportunityContactRole` changes to create and synchronize `Account_Soft_Credit__c` records for organizational accounts. It evaluates non-primary OCRs to identify which org accounts should receive soft credit, filtering for OCRs where `IsPrimary` is false. For Opportunities owned by an organizational account, the handler auto-creates an OCR with the \"Soft Credit\" role for the Opportunity's Primary Contact, ensuring the Contact's soft credit totals reflect the organizational gift without redirecting the hard credit from the Account."
