        "description": "Keeps Campaign Member status in sync with donation progress automatically, removing the need for fundraisers to manually update Campaign Members when a donation closes. When a donation linked to a Campaign closes as won, this handler marks the donor's Campaign Member status as Responded (using the Campaign's first Responded value); for donations still in progress, it sets the first non-Responded status. The Primary Contact Campaign Member Status field on the Opportunity allows overriding this behavior for individual records. This feature is controlled by the Automatic Campaign Member Management setting in NPSP Settings. The source code The handler determines which Campaign Member status value to apply by reading the Campaign's list of available statuses and selecting the first value flagged as `HasResponded = true` for closed-won Opportunities and the first `HasResponded = false` value for open Opportunities. When `Primary_Contact_Campaign_Member_Status__c` is populated on the Opportunity, that explicit value overrides the Campaign's default selection. The `TDTM_ProcessControl` integration prevents re-entrancy when the handler's own update triggers a secondary execution."
