        "description": "Automatically creates and manages Contact Roles on donations, ensuring every gift is properly attributed to the right donors without fundraisers manually adding roles. It enforces NPSP's Contact Role precedence rules: Primary Contact first, then Honoree, Notification Recipient, Affiliated/Related Contact, and finally Household Member. For individual gifts the Primary Contact receives the role configured in NPSP Settings for individual donations; for organizational gifts the organizational role applies. The handler also creates automated soft credits from Relationships and Affiliations, updates donation names per naming settings, syncs Honoree fields, and respects the DisableContactRoleAutomation checkbox for per-record override during data migrations. NPSP includes 12 built-in Contact Role values: Donor, Household Member, Soft Credit, Matched Donor, Honoree, Notification Recipient, Grant Manager, Decision Maker, Influencer, Solicitor, Workplace Giving, and Other. The source code At 898 lines this is one of the largest handlers in the domain, managing the full OCR creation lifecycle across both insert and update paths. On `BeforeInsert` it populates the `Primary_Contact__c` lookup and syncs Honoree and Notification Recipient name fields from their linked Contacts; on `AfterInsert` it upserts primary OCRs, delegates to `OPP_AutomatedSoftCreditsService` for relationship- and affiliation-based roles, and then refreshes the Opportunity Name. The handler respects `DisableContactRoleAutomation__c` as a per-record escape hatch, skipping all OCR logic for any Opportunity where that checkbox is checked, which is the recommended approach for bulk data migrations. Three separate try-catch blocks protect the naming refresh, the soft credit creation, and the household member role creation independently so that a failure in one path does not roll back the others."
