        "description": "Core engine for generating donation names based on configurable naming settings. The default format produces names like \"Barnaby Jones Donation 12/12/21,\" but custom formats can reference any donation field or related record field using `{!FieldName}` syntax — for example, `{!Contact.Name} from {!Contact.MailingCity} gave {!Amount}`. Each naming setting specifies an attribution type (Contact, Organization, or both), applicable record types, a name format pattern, and a date format using Java SimpleDateFormat syntax. If a referenced field is empty, its position in the name is simply omitted. The class validates settings and refreshes names in bulk when configuration changes. The source code The class implements `OPP_INaming` and resolves a naming setting for each Opportunity by matching on Attribution type (Contact, Organization, or both) and scoped Record Types. It uses a regex to locate `{!FieldName}` tokens in the format string and resolves each token against the Opportunity's fields or a related Contact's fields using dynamic `get()` calls. Date fields are formatted using Java `SimpleDateFormat` syntax passed to Apex's `format()` method, and names are truncated at 120 characters if the resolved string exceeds that limit. When the format references a field that is null or empty, the token position is simply omitted rather than raising an error."
