        "description": "Enables fundraisers to send thank-you emails to donors from an individual donation record or in bulk from the \"To Be Acknowledged\" list view. When invoked on a single record, it triggers the email workflow to the Primary Contact and updates the acknowledgment status to \"Acknowledged\" with today's date if the email sends successfully, or to \"Email Acknowledgment Not Sent\" on failure. For batch acknowledgments, users select multiple donations and click Email Acknowledgments to process them simultaneously. The source code The controller sets `Acknowledgment_Status__c` to `\"Email Acknowledgment Now\"` and then updates the records, relying on a Salesforce workflow rule (not Apex) to fire the outbound email. It detects failed sends by re-querying the updated Opportunities and checking which ones still carry the `\"Email Acknowledgment Now\"` status—those whose workflow did not fire—and marks them `\"Email Acknowledgment Not Sent\"`. The entire sequence runs inside a savepoint-rollback block so that a DML exception does not leave records in an inconsistent status mid-batch."
