        "description": "Manages the deployment of the configuration records that map Opportunity Stages to abstract lifecycle states (Pledged, Finalized, etc.). These mappings let administrators customize how NPSP interprets stage transitions — such as when a donation is considered fully paid or when a pledge is committed — without modifying code. NPSP uses these state mappings throughout the system to make decisions based on donation lifecycle state rather than raw stage picklist values. The source code The class deploys `Opportunity_Stage_To_State_Mapping__mdt` records via `CMT_MetadataAPI.deployMetadata()`, using an asynchronous Metadata API call with a registered callback handler rather than synchronous DML. On initial setup it creates two seed records: one mapping the configured \"Opportunity Stage when Fully Paid\" value to the `Finalized` state, and one mapping a `Pledged`-type stage to the `Committed` state. The callback handler stubs both `performSuccessHandler` and `performErrorHandler` as no-ops in the current codebase, meaning deployment failures are silent unless the caller inspects the deployment job status separately."
