        "description": "Translates a donation's Stage picklist value into an abstract NPSP lifecycle state (such as Pledged, Finalized, or Closed) so that NPSP automation can make decisions based on donation state rather than org-specific stage names. Other NPSP components call this utility to determine when to create payments, close pledges, and calculate rollup totals, enabling the same logic to work regardless of how individual organizations name their Opportunity stages. The source code The utility caches the full `Opportunity_Stage_To_State_Mapping__mdt` dataset on first access and exposes `determineOppStateFromOppStage()` for synchronous stage-to-state translation. It stores all stage values associated with each abstract state in `Set<String>` collections, enabling `contains()` checks throughout the codebase without triggering additional queries. The separation from `OPP_StageMappingCMT` keeps runtime lookups isolated from the Metadata API deployment path."
