        "description": "Core class responsible for automatically creating Payment records when donations are inserted or updated. When a donation is saved with a stage set to Posted, it creates a Payment for the full donation amount and marks it as paid in full. The Do Not Automatically Create Payment checkbox on the donation record provides a per-record override, and administrators can also exclude specific record types or Opportunity types in NPSP Settings > Donations > Payments. Payment Field Mappings copy values from donation fields to Payment records automatically, and these mappings apply to auto-created payments and those created through the Payment Wizard, but not to manually created single payments. The source code Payment creation is deferred to the TDTM DML wrapper rather than issued via direct `insert` or `Database.insert` calls, which means the new Payment records are committed atomically within the same save point as the originating Opportunity DML. The class builds `paymentMappings` lazily from `npe01__Payment_Field_Mapping_Settings__c` on first access and validates each mapping for type compatibility before applying it, silently dropping any mapping where field types do not match. The `isNoPaymentForOpp()` guard evaluates three exclusion conditions—`Do_Not_Automatically_Create_Payment__c`, excluded Opportunity Type, and excluded Record Type—in a single boolean expression, so any matching condition suppresses payment creation without further evaluation."
