        "description": "Fires automatically on NPSP Data Import Batch records to enforce batch lifecycle rules. When a new batch is created, it immediately sets the Batch Status to Open. It also prevents modification of any batch that is currently being processed, protecting in-flight imports from configuration changes mid-run. Batch Status values you add manually (such as \"Ready for Review\") will be overwritten to Completed or Failed - Needs Review after NPSP processes the batch. The source code This compact TDTM handler fires on `DataImportBatch__c` insert events and sets `Batch_Status__c` to `'Open'` for new batch records, establishing the initial status that all other status transitions are measured against."
