        "description": "Powers the bulk delete actions on NPSP Data Import list views: Delete All Data Import Records and Delete Imported Data Import Records. Before deleting, it verifies that the running user has the appropriate read and delete permissions, and it returns a clear message if permissions are missing. Admins must add the associated Visualforce page to the user's profile and grant Delete permission on the NPSP Data Imports object. A single delete operation is limited to 10,000 records; larger volumes require Salesforce Data Loader. Import records from active Gift Entry batches should not be deleted through this controller. The source code The delete controller enforces object-level CRUD before deleting, reading `DataImport__c` records by status to scope the delete and issuing `Database.delete()` rather than DML statements, so partial failures are handled per-record rather than rolling back the entire operation."
