        "description": "Drives the BDI settings and import execution page, accessible from the NPSP Data Imports tab via Import All Data Import Records. It allows administrators to view and update the global import configuration (batch size, contact matching rules, donation matching behavior, date range), kick off a full import run, and start a dry-run preview that evaluates open Opportunities and unpaid Payments for potential matches without actually processing any records. Only System Administrators should use this import execution interface. The source code This Visualforce controller supports both batch-scoped and record-list-scoped import paths: when a set of DataImport IDs has been pre-selected (via the `disPopulated()` check), it calls `BDI_DataImport_API.processDataImportRecords()` directly; otherwise it enqueues a full `BDI_DataImport_BATCH` job. The same branching applies for dry-run validation, allowing the Import All and Dry Run buttons to share the same underlying execution paths. Job status polling is performed by re-reading the `AsyncApexJob` record each time the page refreshes, surfacing `TotalJobItems`, `JobItemsProcessed`, and `NumberOfErrors` without requiring a streaming connection."
