        "description": "Handles Opportunity and Payment creation, matching, and updating during BDI processing. It maps import row fields for donation amount, date, stage, and campaign to Opportunity and Payment records, and applies the configurable Donation Matching Rule to find existing gifts within a date window you set. When all Payments on an Opportunity are marked paid, the Opportunity Stage is automatically set to the value you configured in \"Opportunity Stage When Fully Paid.\" The class also manages dry-run preview fields that show which donations would be matched before you commit the import. Gift records coming from Salesforce.org Elevate are handled separately since their payment lifecycle is managed externally. The source code The donation import sequence begins by reading `Donation_Matching_Behavior__c` from settings to determine how strictly matches must resolve. Elevate-sourced DataImport records are separated into their own processing list because their payment lifecycle is managed externally and they skip the standard `iMatchDonations.match()` call. For each non-Elevate record, the code validates that the resolved matching result satisfies the configured behavior (raising `bdiErrorDonationLookupMatch`, `bdiErrorDonationRequireNoMatch`, `bdiErrorDonationNoMatch`, `bdiErrorDonationMultiMatch`, or `bdiErrorDonationRequireNoMatch` as appropriate) before allowing an upsert of the Opportunity. The `dataImportFieldToPaymentField` field-mapping dictionary is lazily populated on first access via `bdi.mapDataImportFields('Payment', 'npe01__OppPayment__c', ...)`, which means the same mapping infrastructure that resolves Contact and Account fields also drives Payment field population. The \"Apply New Payment\" flow is handled as a special case by pre-seeding `paymentsByDataImportId` with an empty payment linked to the matched Opportunity, bypassing the normal match cycle."
