        "description": "Powers the Advanced Mapping administration UI, accessed via NPSP Settings under System Tools > Advanced Mapping for Data Import & Gift Entry. It retrieves Object Groups and their field mappings, creates new field and object mappings saved as configuration records, and validates namespace compatibility. Admins must have this class added to their Enabled Apex Classes to access the interface. The UI supports creating custom Object Groups for objects not mapped by default — any object related to Contacts, Accounts, or Opportunities can be added. Changes are deployed asynchronously, and the UI polls for completion status before confirming success. The source code The Advanced Mapping UI controller exposes `@AuraEnabled` methods for creating, updating, and deleting `Data_Import_Field_Mapping__mdt` and `Data_Import_Object_Mapping__mdt` records, each routing through `BDI_MigrationMappingUtility.enqueueMetadataRecords()` for deployment. The inner `ComboboxOption` class implements `Comparable` so that field and object name lists can be sorted alphabetically using `List.sort()` before being returned to the UI, avoiding client-side sorting. The controller handles the asynchronous nature of metadata deployment by returning the deployment ID to the caller, which the UI then polls against a `DeploymentEvent__e` subscription."
