        "sourceUrl": "https://github.com/SalesforceFoundation/NPSP/blob/main/force-app/main/default/classes/BDI_MappingService.cls",
        "description": "The abstract foundation shared by both field mapping implementations in the BDI framework. It defines the interface contract that both the Advanced Mapping approach (recommended, using configuration metadata) and the legacy help-text approach must implement. Advanced Mapping reads mappings from stored configuration records and supports any Salesforce object and field. The legacy help-text approach reads mapping references embedded in the staging field help text in the format ObjectGroup.FieldAPIName. The source code This abstract virtual class defines the `getFieldMap()` method contract used by both `BDI_MappingServiceAdvanced` and `BDI_MappingServiceHelpText`, along with a `targetFieldsBySourceField` map property that is populated during initialization and consulted by `BDI_DataImportFLSService` to resolve which target object fields correspond to each DataImport source field for FLS validation purposes."
