        "sourceUrl": "https://github.com/SalesforceFoundation/NPSP/blob/main/force-app/main/default/classes/BDI_MappingServiceHelpText.cls",
        "description": "The legacy field mapping implementation that reads mapping instructions from the help text of staging fields, using the format ObjectGroup.FieldAPIName (for example, Contact1.Preferred_Name__c). It parses each field's help text to determine which target object and field receives the value, and handles multi-currency code mappings. This approach supports only a limited set of objects compared to Advanced Mapping — GAU Allocation and Recurring Donation mappings are not supported, and mapping two staging fields to the same target field can cause overwrite conflicts. Orgs are encouraged to migrate to Advanced Mapping. This implementation is maintained for backward compatibility and the migration can be performed automatically through the Advanced Mapping enablement wizard. The source code This legacy implementation resolves field mappings by reading the inline help text of each `DataImport__c` field using `DescribeFieldResult.getInlineHelpText()`, then parsing the string as `\"{objectToken}.{fieldName}\"`. Fields whose help text does not match that two-part pattern are silently skipped. A small set of known standard help-text mappings (hardcoded in the utility class) are excluded from the parsed results to avoid collisions with manually managed fields. The class also supports `addMappedField()` for callers that need to inject additional mappings programmatically without touching field metadata."
