        "description": "Enables processing a specific subset of NPSP Data Import records from a list view, rather than processing all unprocessed records at once. Admins select specific rows, click Import Selected Data Import Records, and only those records are submitted for processing. This is useful for reprocessing previously failed records after resolving the underlying issues documented in the Failure Information field — failed records are included in the eligible set alongside unprocessed ones. After processing, the controller returns users to the list view. The source code This controller reads selected DataImport record IDs from the page parameters and calls `BDI_DataImport_API.processDataImportRecords()` for those specific records. It validates that all selected records are in an importable status before starting the job, failing gracefully with a user-facing message if no eligible records are found."
