        "description": "Powers the BDI matching settings page by exposing the six donation matching behavior options for selection: Do Not Match (always create new records), No Match (fail if a match exists), Single Match (requires exactly one match), Single Match or Create (matches one or creates new), Best Match (requires at least one match and picks the closest), and Best Match or Create (matches or creates if none found). These settings apply globally to every feature using NPSP Data Importer, including Gift Entry and Elevate. When a strict matching mode (No Match, Single Match, Best Match) cannot find an Opportunity or Payment match, the import row shows as Failed, though associated Contacts and Accounts are still created successfully. The source code This controller exposes the six donation matching behavior options as `@RemoteAction` getter methods so the Visualforce settings page can populate picklist values without a round-trip to custom metadata, using the global constants defined in `BDI_DataImport_API` as the canonical source."
