        "description": "Test stub that simulates the Elevate payment service connection during automated testing, allowing Gift Entry components to be tested in isolation without a live payment gateway or valid credentials. Test methods use a builder pattern to control whether the mock reports the org as an Elevate customer, enabling accurate simulation of both Elevate-connected and non-connected scenarios for components like the card tokenization widget and form renderer. The source code This mock uses a builder pattern via `withIsElevateCustomer` that returns `this`, enabling fluent test setup syntax. Because it implements `StubProvider.handleMethodCall`, all method calls on the stub are intercepted generically, so the mock can be evolved to cover additional `GE_PaymentServices` methods without adding new interface methods — a design that trades compile-time safety for flexibility in test scenarios."
