        "description": "The primary service for the Customizable Rollups framework, exposing methods to retrieve rollup definitions, check whether Customizable Rollups are enabled, execute rollups on demand, and signal that rollup state needs recalculation. When Customizable Rollups are not enabled, the system uses the legacy fixed rollup engine and approximately 87 out-of-box definitions. This service is the main entry point for any external code interacting with the rollup subsystem, including the scheduling of nightly batch jobs. It also handles configuration change events when rollup definitions are updated through the admin interface. The source code This class is declared `without sharing` and contains a nested `ApiException` that extends `Exception`, used to surface both parameter validation errors and processing failures with formatted custom label messages. It bridges to an optional \"Archive Bridge\" integration package via the Callable API pattern, calling `archiveBridgeConfig.getCallableApi().call('dso.getRollupStateForRecords', params)` and `'dso.setRollupStateAsStale'` to retrieve or invalidate persisted rollup state stored by that external package; when the Archive Bridge is not installed, `isRollupStateEnabled()` returns false and all state operations are silently skipped. The class also builds `RollupUtil` and `FilterGroupUtil` inner classes that diff incoming CMT objects against the currently deployed metadata to determine which `RollupType` enums are affected by a pending configuration change, then passes those changed type names through `getCallbackHandler()` to the enablement pipeline."
