        "description": "The shared foundation for all Customizable Rollups batch jobs, providing common infrastructure for query construction, error handling, and Payment rollup detection. All CRLP batch jobs inherit from this base class, either through the standard processing subclass or the high-volume processing subclass. It also supports Incremental Mode, where nightly batches are scoped to only records with gifts modified within a configurable number of days, and handles the case where organizations have not enabled Partial Soft Credits by synthesizing equivalent data from existing Contact Role records. The source code This abstract class defines the shared infrastructure inherited by every CRLP batch job, including `BatchQueryBuilder`, an inner class with its own lazy properties for incremental query mode. The `BatchQueryBuilder` appends a `LAST_N_DAYS:N` filter to the detail query when `Rollups_IncrementalLastNDays_ValOverride__c` and `Rollups_IncrementalLastNDays_FldOverride__c` are set in the Custom Settings, enabling a configurable incremental rollup mode where only recently modified records are re-processed rather than the full history. It also contains `matchOrBuildPartialSoftCredit()`, which synthesizes `Partial_Soft_Credit__c` SObjects from `OpportunityContactRole` records on the fly when the organization has not enabled the Partial Soft Credit feature, allowing the same downstream processing logic to run uniformly. Error handling is routed through `ERR_Handler` and `ERR_Handler_API`, with a dedicated `CRLPBatchException` inner class for batch-layer failures."
