        "description": "Manages saving Customizable Rollup configuration changes — rollup definitions and filter group/rule changes — so they take effect across the org. Changes are queued for deployment and submitted together in a single operation. Rollup and filter group definitions saved this way can be promoted from Sandbox to Production, though NPSP's built-in out-of-box rollups cannot be deployed using change sets. This service is called by the rollup configuration UI when administrators save new or modified definitions, and it notifies the enablement pipeline when deployment completes so batch jobs can be rescheduled if needed. The source code This service is the deployment gateway for all CRLP configuration changes, maintaining a static `queuedMetadataTypes` list that accumulates `Metadata.CustomMetadata` instances from callers before `deployedQueuedMetadataTypes()` submits them as a single Metadata API deployment container. The overloaded `deployedQueuedMetadataTypes()` variant that accepts a `CMT_MetadataAPI.MetadataCallbackHandler` wires a `CMT_MetadataAPI.MetadataCallBack` callback object to the deployment, allowing `CRLP_EnablementService.RollupMetadataHandler` to receive the async completion notification and take post-deployment action such as rescheduling batch jobs."
