        "description": "Defines the approximately 87 standard Customizable Rollup definitions that ship with NPSP, covering the rollup fields on Account, Contact, Household, and Recurring Donation objects. These out-of-box rollups include donation totals, averages, first and last close dates, best gift year, membership join and end dates, membership level, soft credit amounts (total, this year, last year, two years ago), and N-Day rollups. This class is used when CRLP is first enabled or when an administrator clicks Reset to Defaults in NPSP Settings to restore the standard configuration. The source code This class contains hardcoded definitions for approximately 87 default rollup configurations using a `List<List<Object>>` data structure with 182 list allocations, one per rollup field mapping. Each inner list encodes the summary object, summary field, detail object, amount field, date field, operation type, time-bound operation, and filter group name for a single rollup, which `CRLP_DefaultConfigBuilder_SVC` then translates into `CRLP_RollupCMT.Rollup` objects for deployment as `Rollup__mdt` Custom Metadata records."
