        "description": "Converts your existing rollup customizations — excluded Opportunity record types, excluded Opportunity types, soft credit role settings, fiscal year preferences, N-Day values, and User Defined Rollups — into equivalent Customizable Rollups configuration when you first enable the feature. This means your existing rollup behavior is preserved as editable definitions after the switch, rather than being lost. Household User Defined Rollups are not converted because the Household object is deprecated in the Household Account Model. NPSP Settings pages for User Defined Rollups and Donor Statistics are removed after conversion. The source code This service converts legacy `RLLP` and `npo02__User_Rollup_Field_Settings__c` configurations into CRLP-compatible CMT structures during the initial CRLP enablement flow. It reads existing record type configurations, excluded opportunity types, and soft credit role lists from household custom settings, then maps them onto the filter group and filter rule schema used by CRLP, effectively migrating an org's customizations from the legacy rollup engine to the metadata-driven system without manual reconfiguration. The `softDeleteExtra*` private methods handle downgrade scenarios, soft-deleting rollup records and filter groups that exist in NPSP defaults but are not applicable to the current org's configuration."
