        "description": "Manages the full lifecycle of enabling, disabling, and resetting the Customizable Rollups feature, accessed through NPSP Settings under Donations. Enabling converts all existing out-of-box and User Defined Rollups, schedules all 13 nightly batch jobs (staggered from 11 p.m.), and deploys rollup definitions. Disabling preserves your customizations but switches back to legacy rollup processing. Resetting wipes all customizations and restores the NPSP defaults as they were when you first enabled Customizable Rollups. The source code This class manages the full lifecycle of enabling, disabling, and resetting the CRLP feature and calls `UTIL_Permissions.checkPermission()` before any state change, throwing a `UTIL_Permissions`-typed exception with the custom label `stgCRLPNonAdminError` if the running user is not a system administrator. The `enable()` method upserts `Customizable_Rollup_Settings__c`, deploys default CMT records via `CRLP_DefaultConfigBuilder_SVC`, and optionally reschedules the NPSP nightly batch jobs via `UTIL_MasterSchedulableHelper`; telemetry is tracked via `UTIL_OrgTelemetry_SVC`. The nested `RollupMetadataHandler` implements `CMT_MetadataAPI.MetadataCallbackHandler` to receive the asynchronous callback after the Metadata API deployment completes, at which point it updates the deployment status field on Custom Settings and, on success, triggers batch job rescheduling."
