        "description": "Provides consistent fiscal year boundary calculations for all time-bound rollup operations, ensuring that rollups using \"Best Year,\" \"Years Donated,\" or \"Years Ago\" time frames reflect your organization's fiscal year rather than the calendar year. NPSP requires the Salesforce Standard Fiscal Year (not Custom Fiscal Years) with the \"based on ending month\" setting for rollups to calculate correctly. The Use Fiscal Year option on a rollup definition appears when the operation involves year-based time frames. The source code This class resolves the tension between calendar-year and fiscal-year rollup reporting by querying the Organization record's `FiscalYearStartMonth` and `UsesStartDateAsFiscalYearName` fields once and caching the result in a static lazy property. The `getFiscalYear()` method builds the fiscal year boundary dates by anchoring on that start month and shifts backward one year if the target date precedes the current fiscal year start, then returns either the start year or the end year of the fiscal period depending on the org's naming convention. Only standard (non-custom) fiscal years are supported."
