        "description": "Defines the ten rollup operations available when configuring a rollup definition and specifies which Salesforce field data types each operation supports. Sum totals Amount Field values; Average computes the mean; Count tallies matching records; Largest and Smallest find the max and min values; First and Last return the value from the earliest or latest record (using Created Date as a tie-breaker for same-date records); Best Year returns the four-digit year with the largest total; Years Donated returns unique years separated by semicolons; Donor Streak counts consecutive years with qualifying records. It also determines which operations support time-bound variants such as Days Back and Years Ago. The source code This enum-backed class defines the ten available rollup operation types (Sum, Average, Count, Largest, Smallest, Newest, Oldest, Best Year, Best Year Total, Years Donated) and the set of field data types compatible with each, using a static map keyed by operation to prevent incompatible configurations from reaching the calculation layer."
