        "description": "Executes the actual math for a single rollup operation against one detail record, updating the running calculation state for that rollup. For aggregate operations, Sum adds up Amount Field values, Average computes the mean, and Count tallies qualifying records. For single-result operations (First, Last, Largest, Smallest), it captures the Field to Roll Up value from the identified record, using Created Date as a tie-breaker when multiple records share the same date. Best Year computes the four-digit year with the largest gift total; Donor Streak counts consecutive calendar or fiscal years with qualifying giving. Multi-currency conversion is applied automatically, and errors in individual records are contained so one malformed record cannot abort an entire batch. The source code This service class executes the per-record mathematical operation for a single `CRLP_Rollup` state object against one detail record, routing to `processSingleResultRollups()` for Newest, Oldest, Largest, and Smallest operations or to `handleRollupAggregation()` for Sum, Average, Count, and time-bound variants. Multi-currency conversion is applied inside `convertAmountToCurrency()` using `UTIL_CurrencyConversion`, and the three try-catch blocks guard against null field references, unsupported operation states, and currency conversion failures—all caught and swallowed to prevent a single malformed record from aborting an entire batch scope."
