        "description": "Powers the Recalculate Rollups button on Account, Contact, GAU, and Recurring Donation record pages, triggering an immediate rollup recalculation for a single record without waiting for the next nightly batch. The recalculation runs in the background; users should refresh the page after a few minutes to see the updated values. If the button is not visible, the administrator needs to add it to the appropriate page layouts. This is the recommended way to force a rollup update on a specific record after making corrections or when diagnosing a data discrepancy. The source code This Visualforce controller handles the on-demand recalculate button present on Account, Contact, GAU, and Recurring Donation record pages. In trigger-safe contexts (batch, future, or queueable), it calls `CRLP_RollupQueueable.runRollupsForIds()` directly; otherwise it calls `System.enqueueJob(new CRLP_RollupQueueable(recordId))`, routing Contact Soft Credit recalculations through a separate `calculateContactSoftCredit()` path that handles the OCR/PSC join that standard rollup processing does not cover in the synchronous path."
