        "description": "Manages the creation, validation, and deployment of rollup definitions, filter groups, and filter rules as configuration records. It generates unique developer names, detects duplicates, checks whether a definition has changed since it was last saved, and builds records ready for deployment through the Salesforce Metadata API. Rollup and filter group definitions saved through this class can be promoted from Sandbox to Production. Important: never modify, deactivate, or delete the key fields or rollups used by the nightly batch jobs, as doing so can cause system limit issues. The source code This class is the object model for all Custom Metadata Type records used by CRLP, providing `FilterGroup`, `FilterRule`, and `Rollup` inner classes that each expose a `getMetadataRecord()` method returning a `Metadata.CustomMetadata` instance ready for deployment via `CMT_MetadataAPI`. The four try-catch blocks guard JSON serialization and field describe calls during CMT record construction, and the `generateHash()` private method on `FilterRule` creates a deterministic developer name from field values to ensure idempotent record naming across repeated deployments."
