        "description": "The main rollup calculation engine that coordinates the full calculation for a set of summary records. It accepts summary records, detail records, payment records, rollup definitions, and processing options through a builder-style configuration, then delegates to the appropriate credit-type handler and writes results back to the database. It also automatically flags records for high-volume processing when their gift counts exceed the threshold, so future batch runs route them correctly. This is the central processing hub called by both batch and trigger-based rollup execution. The source code Declared as `inherited sharing`, this 696-line class is the core rollup calculation coordinator, using a fluent builder pattern with `with*()` methods before `startRollupProcessing()` is called. The `isSkewModeNeeded()` method checks whether the summary record's `npo02__NumberOfClosedOpps__c` meets or exceeds the threshold from `Rollups_Limit_on_Attached_Opps_for_Skew__c` and, if so, sets `CustomizableRollups_UseSkewMode__c = true` on the record so future batch runs route it to the skew pipeline automatically. The `cachedHandlerInstanceByRollupType` static map avoids reinstantiating the virtual handler class per parent record, and `initializeExternalRollupStateData()` integrates with the Archive Bridge via `CRLP_ApiService` to seed rollup state from externally stored data before accumulation begins."
