        "description": "Constructs the queries for fetching detail (gift) records during rollup processing, supporting Payment sub-queries, parent ID filtering, Incremental Mode date filters, and sort ordering. It uses a builder-style configuration to assemble the query based on rollup type and processing mode. The resulting queries are used by both batch job start methods and real-time rollup processing. The source code This class constructs the detail-record SOQL for both Skew Mode and Non-Skew Mode runs, using `useIncrementalMode` to conditionally append a `LAST_N_DAYS` filter. The `buildDetailsQuery()` method branches on whether the rollup type is a soft credit (routing through `buildDetailsQuerySoftCredits()`) or a hard credit (routing through `buildDetailsQueryHardCredits()`), and the `withSummaryRecordIdsVar()` fluent option injects a named bind variable into the query string rather than a literal Id set, enabling the result to be passed directly to `Database.getQueryLocator()` in batch context."
