        "description": "Executes rollup calculations asynchronously for a set of parent record IDs, deferring the work to a background job so gift entry transactions are not slowed down. The real-time trigger and on-demand recalculation both use this class to queue rollup work for after the main transaction completes. When there are more records to process than can fit in one job, the class automatically chains itself to continue processing in a subsequent job. The source code This class implements `System.Queueable` and holds a `List<List<Id>>` as a queue of summary record Id batches. The `execute()` method pops the first inner list, processes those records through `CRLP_RollupProcessor`, commits results via `CRLP_RollupProcessor_SVC.updateChangedRecordsWithLogging()`, then calls `System.enqueueJob(new CRLP_RollupQueueable(this.queueOfSummaryIds))` to chain itself if more batches remain—implementing a self-chaining queueable pattern that processes all affected parents in sequence from a single trigger invocation."
