        "description": "Provides utility methods used across the Customizable Rollups framework: determining whether active rollup definitions exist for each credit type (Payment, Soft Credit, Partial Soft Credit, Account Soft Credit), mapping rollup types to their summary and detail objects, and identifying the max related Opportunity count that determines when a record switches to high-volume processing. The service also performs change detection to skip database writes when rollup totals have not actually changed, reducing unnecessary updates. The source code Declared as a plain class (not `inherited sharing`), this class provides the `IRollupHandler` interface definition that `CRLP_VRollupHandler` implements, establishes `isCustomizableRollupEngineEnabled` as a lazy static Boolean checked by trigger handlers before executing any CRLP code path, and supplies `resultsNeedUpdate()` which compares old and new summary SObject values field-by-field to avoid unnecessary DML when rollup totals have not changed. The `CRLP_Exception` inner class is the base exception type for the CRLP framework, and the four try-catch blocks in the class guard describe calls and namespace lookups during static initialization."
