        "description": "The real-time trigger handler that fires whenever an Opportunity or Payment is created, updated, deleted, or restored, initiating immediate rollup recalculation for affected Accounts, Contacts, and GAU records. It checks whether any rollup-relevant fields actually changed before doing work, avoiding unnecessary processing on unrelated updates. When Customizable Rollups are not enabled, this handler does not fire and the system uses the legacy rollup handler instead. In high-frequency scenarios, it guards against queuing too many background recalculation jobs at once. Rollup values that are recalculated by this handler include Amount, Stage, and Close Date changes on related gifts. The source code This TDTM handler is registered on both `Opportunity` and `npe01__OppPayment__c` objects and is the primary entry point for real-time CRLP rollup initiation from DML events. When the trigger fires, `isRollupRecalcNeeded()` checks whether any field included in an active rollup definition has actually changed before proceeding, avoiding unnecessary downstream work on unrelated Opportunity updates. In contexts where the caller is already in a batch, future, or queueable execution, the handler calls `CRLP_RollupQueueable.runRollupsForIds()` synchronously within that context; in a synchronous trigger context, it builds a `List<List<Id>>` queue grouped by summary object type (Account, Contact, RD) and enqueues a single `CRLP_RollupQueueable`, checking `Limits.getQueueableJobs()` against the org limit and querying `AsyncApexJob` to ensure no more than five CRLP queueable jobs are already pending before dispatching."
