        "description": "Identifies all parent records (Accounts, Contacts, GAUs, Recurring Donations) that require high-volume rollup processing and launches the appropriate high-volume batch jobs. It queries the full org for records exceeding the Skew Mode Threshold or with the Force Skew Mode field set, collects their IDs, and dispatches them to the correct specialized batch class in groups of 300 (configurable via Skew Mode Dispatcher Size in NPSP Settings). This dispatcher drives all six high-volume batch job types: Account Hard Credit, Account Soft Credit, Account-level Contact Soft Credit, Contact Hard Credit, Contact Soft Credit, GAU, and Recurring Donations. The source code Declared as both `Batchable` and `Stateful`, this dispatcher queries all summary records across the full org and, for each one, records its Id in a stateful list if it meets the skew criteria. In `finish()`, it calls `CRLP_RollupBatch_SVC.executeBatchRollupJob()` with the collected skew-eligible Id list and the `SkewMode` flag, launching the appropriate concrete skew batch class. The configurable batch size (`Rollups_Skew_Dispatcher_Batch_Size__c`, defaulting to 300) controls how many summary records are evaluated per execute chunk, with the stateful collection accumulating across all chunks before the final dispatch in `finish()`."
