        "description": "The abstract base class that all six object-specific rollup handler services (Account, Contact, GAU, RD, SoftCredit, and Account Soft Credit) extend, providing shared rollup processing infrastructure. It manages rollup definition initialization, currency code handling, grouped rollup construction, result population, and Opportunity ID tracking. Subclasses inherit these shared mechanics and implement only the pieces specific to their target object. The source code This virtual class implements `CRLP_Rollup_SVC.IRollupHandler` and serves as the abstract base for the seven object-specific handler services (Account, Contact, AccSoftCredit, SoftCredit, GAU, RD, and the infra variant). The `setRecordId()` method calls the virtual `initRollup()` override, allowing subclasses to initialize their rollup definition lists at binding time; `buildGroupedRollups()` populates the handler's rollup list from `CRLP_Rollup_SEL` filtered to the specific rollup type and optionally the `RollupTypeFilter` discriminator. The `resetAllRollups()` method zeroes all accumulators on the `CRLP_Rollup` instances held by the handler, enabling the same handler instance to be reused across parent records within a batch scope."
