        "description": "Calculates Partial Soft Credit rollup totals for Contact and Account records in the legacy rollup engine, computing soft credit amounts for this year, last year, two years ago, and all time. Partial Soft Credits allow split recognition across multiple contacts — for example, when two board members each receive 50% credit for a contribution they jointly cultivated. It respects the Always Roll Up to Primary Contact setting and the N-Day window, and applies Individual Account filtering for correct Contact-level routing. The source code This class handles the legacy soft credit rollup calculation path, independently querying both `Partial_Soft_Credit__c` and `OpportunityContactRole` records for a list of Contacts and then applying precedence logic: if a PSC record exists for an OCR, the PSC amount is used; if no PSC exists and the OCR is not a hard credit role, the OCR's proportional amount is used instead. Fiscal year boundary dates are computed by inspecting the org's fiscal year settings, and multi-currency amounts are converted before accumulation. Results are written back via `UTIL_DMLService`, routing errors to `ERR_Handler_API`."
