        "description": "The original legacy rollup calculation engine, computing approximately 87 out-of-box rollup fields on Account, Contact, and Household records: donation totals, averages, largest and smallest gifts, first and last close dates, best gift year, membership stats, N-Day values, and soft credit amounts. It includes both synchronous and asynchronous processing paths, plus User Defined Rollup support for custom calculations on Opportunity fields. Legacy rollups work only against Contact Roles (not Payment records or Partial Soft Credits) and do not support Advanced Currency Management. When Customizable Rollups are enabled, this class acts as a thin routing shim that immediately hands off to the Customizable Rollups engine, maintaining backward compatibility for any existing trigger entry points. The source code Declared `without sharing`, this 1,119-line class is the original NPSP rollup engine, predating CRLP by several major releases. It defines `@future` static methods (`rollupContactsandHouseholdsForTriggerFuture`, `rollupAccountsFuture`, `rollupContactsFuture`, `rollupHouseholdsFuture`) as asynchronous fallback paths when the calling context cannot immediately execute synchronous DML, and a `shouldRunImmediate()` guard avoids re-queuing when already in a batch, future, or queueable context. When CRLP is enabled, `isCustomizableRollupsEnabled` causes most code paths to delegate to `CRLP_RollupQueueable.runRollupsForIds()` instead, making this class a thin routing shim for backward-compatible trigger entry points."
