        "description": "The single entry point for all automation that fires when Engagement Plan records are created, updated, or deleted. It follows NPSP's one-trigger-per-object pattern and delegates to TDTM-configured handlers rather than containing logic itself. The primary handlers it activates are the plan engine -- which validates the target lookup on before-insert and generates all Task records from the template on after-insert -- and any other handlers that may be configured for the Engagement Plan object. Using the TDTM framework means these handlers run in a predictable order and can be toggled on or off through NPSP Settings."
