        "description": "The single entry point for all automation that fires when Engagement Plan Task definition records (the template steps) are created, updated, or deleted. It routes to the validation handler, which checks for circular dependencies and cross-template parent references before any task definition change is saved. Note that the task dependency cascade automation and task rollup automation are registered on the standard Salesforce Task object instead of here, because those handlers respond to staff completing live tasks rather than to administrators editing template definitions."
