        "name": "Error_Settings__c",
        "label": "Error Settings",
        "relationships": [],
        "description": "The configuration object that controls how NPSP handles and reports errors across your org. You manage all these settings in NPSP Settings > System Tools > Error Notifications. Key options include: Store Errors (enables saving Error records to the Error Log), Error Notifications On and Error Notifications To (enables email alerts and designates who receives them), and Disable Error Handling (turns off the entire error framework if needed for troubleshooting). The Respect Duplicate Rule Settings option, also found on this settings page, is a prerequisite for the Contact Merge feature. When a designated System Administrator is deactivated, NPSP automatically clears the notification recipient field so alerts are never silently lost. Additional settings on this object manage debug mode, async error check scheduling, and health check behavior.",
