    "lwcs": [
      {
        "name": "errRecordLog",
        "imports": [],
        "description": "The Error Log UI component embedded in NPSP Settings > System Tools > Error Log, giving administrators a dedicated interface for reviewing and investigating NPSP errors. It displays each logged error's date and time, type, full message, affected object type, a clickable link to the record that caused the error, and a stack trace for deeper debugging -- the same fields documented in Salesforce's official NPSP troubleshooting guide. Error records only appear here when \"Store Errors\" is enabled in your Error Notifications settings. The component can also be placed directly on any Salesforce record page to scope the error log to errors related to that specific record rather than showing org-wide errors. The source code The component uses the `@wire(getObjectInfo)` adapter to dynamically resolve field labels and help text from the `Error__c` schema at runtime rather than hard-coding label strings, which means column headers in the error log table reflect whatever the org's field metadata says (including any admin customization). It extends `NavigationMixin` and provides two navigation paths: one to the parent record that caused the error and one to the `Error__c` record itself. Eleven imported custom labels drive all UI strings, and the component exposes a single `@api recordId` property, making it embeddable on any record page to scope the error log to that specific record rather than showing org-wide errors.",
        "sourceUrl": "https://github.com/SalesforceFoundation/NPSP/tree/main/force-app/main/default/lwc/errRecordLog"
      }
    ],
