        "description": "Schedulable class that serves as the nightly cron entry point for running the Level Assignment batch job, registered by default as scheduled job \"NPSP 08 - Level Assignment Updates.\" When it fires, it reads the configured batch size from NPSP Settings and launches the Level Assignment batch job. This job runs as part of the NPSP nightly batch sequence so donor levels stay current without manual intervention. Administrators can reschedule or remove this job from Setup > Scheduled Jobs; it is automatically recreated when you visit NPSP Settings > Bulk Data Processes > Batch Process Settings."
