        "description": "Controller class backing the Manage Soft Credits page, which is accessed through the Manage Soft Credits button on both the Opportunity page layout and the Partial Soft Credits related list. The page displays all Contacts who already have Contact Roles on the Opportunity and lets users toggle each between Full (100% of the Opportunity amount) and Partial (a custom amount) soft credit mode. You can browse for additional Contacts to credit through the Add Another Soft Credit action, and validation checks ensure totals are correct before saving. When adding new Partial Soft Credits, only Contact Roles eligible for soft credit rollups appear unless Customizable Rollups is enabled, in which case all roles are shown. The page also supports an option to allow combined soft credit amounts to exceed the Opportunity total, for cases where this legitimately occurs. Amounts can be entered as absolute currency values or as percentages of the Opportunity total. The Manage Soft Credits Visualforce page must be explicitly granted to user profiles through Visualforce Page Access settings. The source code The save operation uses an explicit `Database.setSavepoint()` and `Database.rollback()` pattern rather than relying on implicit transaction boundaries, allowing the controller to perform partial-error detection across two separate delete passes (PSC records first, then OCR records) and roll back the entire operation if either pass encounters failures. Amounts can be entered either as absolute currency values or as percentages of the Opportunity total, with `convertAmountToPercentage` and `convertPercentageToAmount` methods handling the conversion at two decimal places using `HALF_UP` rounding. Before DML, the controller pre-validates each SoftCredit row's contact lookup, amount, and role for completeness, building in-memory rollback snapshots of both the `contactRole` and `partial` objects via `clone(true, true, true, true)` so the page state can be restored without a re-query if the transaction fails."
