        "description": "Trigger handler that fires on Opportunity changes to keep related Partial Soft Credit and Account Soft Credit records in sync with their parent Opportunity. In organizations using Multiple Currencies, it updates the currency on all child soft credit records whenever the Opportunity's currency changes — without this synchronization, the nightly soft credit rollup calculations would aggregate amounts in mismatched currencies and produce incorrect totals. This handler also participates in the Matching Gift workflow: when a Matching Gift Opportunity is created, Partial Soft Credits are automatically generated for each matched donor's original gift amount, and this handler ensures those records stay current if the Opportunity is subsequently modified. In single-currency organizations the handler performs no work at all. The source code The handler uses `UserInfo.isMultiCurrencyOrganization()` as a guard before performing any work, making it a true no-op in single-currency orgs with zero overhead. Currency propagation is implemented using dynamic SOQL strings (via `Database.query`) and `SObject.put('CurrencyIsoCode', ...)` rather than typed field references, making the same `updateSoftCreditCurrencyFromParent` utility method reusable for both `Partial_Soft_Credit__c` and `Account_Soft_Credit__c` without duplication."
