        "description": "Configuration reader class that provides centralized access to all Elevate integration settings needed for API communication. It exposes individual configuration values — API key, endpoint root, client ID, merchant IDs, gateway IDs, SDK URL — as well as permission and status checks that let any calling code confirm whether the Elevate integration is properly configured and active before attempting a callout. It also provides the URL prefix for constructing links back to the Elevate dashboard. This class is the single source of truth for Elevate configuration, consumed by the request builder, commitment request builder, gateway service, and all other components that communicate with Elevate. The source code The class reads configuration from `Payment_Services_Configuration__c` without relying on hierarchy custom settings, instead querying records keyed by `Service__c` and `Key__c` — meaning gateway IDs, merchant IDs, API keys, and the SDK URL are all stored as individual rows rather than fields on a single settings record. The `hasIntegrationPermissions` check is pre-computed and stored as an instance variable (`hasPermissions`), avoiding repeated permission lookups across a single transaction's chain of callout-preparation calls."
