        "description": "Data class that builds and manages the context metadata sent to Elevate alongside payment and commitment requests. Elevate transactions carry origin tracking fields — Origin ID, Origin Name, and Origin Type (Engagement Hub, Giving Page, Payments API, or Salesforce) — as well as UTM parameters for Google Analytics attribution so your organization can report on which campaigns and channels are driving online donations. The class provides methods to set the donation source context and attach campaign attribution, and a merge method that combines new metadata with any previously stored values to prevent overwriting unrelated tracking fields during updates. The serialization method converts the metadata into the format expected by the Elevate API request body so NPSP-specific context travels with every transaction for downstream reporting and analytics. The source code The `mergeWithExistingMetadata` method applies a last-write-wins merge strategy: existing metadata is placed into the result map first, then the new metadata overwrites any overlapping keys. This ensures that UTM parameters or origin type set by the online donation form can be selectively overridden by NPSP-side context (such as a campaign ID added during Gift Entry) without losing unrelated attribution fields. The `toUntypedMap` serializes only populated properties (origin and campaign are conditionally included), keeping the API payload minimal when attribution data is absent."
