        "description": "Builds a structured view of field-level changes on a Recurring Donation record by comparing old and new values for key fields like Amount, Installments, Campaign, and Installment Period. The change log automatically assigns a Change Type of \"Upgrade\" or \"Downgrade\" when Amount or Annual Value changes; Status, Campaign, and Payment Method changes are also recorded but without automatic Change Type assignment. It produces a change view that feeds the audit trail stored in the Recurring Donation Change Log object. This class works in coordination with the change log service to detect and record modifications. The source code The class compares old and new values for around 30 tracked fields — including Amount, AnnualValue, ExpectedTotalValue, Campaign, Status, InstallmentPeriod, Frequency, PaymentMethod, RecurringType, and PlannedInstallments — and automatically assigns a ChangeType of Upgrade or Downgrade only when monetary fields change, leaving status and method changes without an automatic type. It holds previous-and-new pairs for each tracked field, feeding a structured view into RecurringDonationChangeLog__c rather than relying on platform field history."
