        "description": "Provides the shared batch processing framework for migrating Legacy Recurring Donation records to the Enhanced format. It handles error aggregation, batch execution flow, and field mapping across the many Legacy Recurring Donation fields. Both the dry-run and actual migration batch classes extend this base to reuse its core logic. The source code This abstract batch class implements Database.Batchable, Database.Stateful, and Schedulable simultaneously, making it the orchestration point for the multi-step Legacy-to-Enhanced migration. It calls `TDTM_Config_API.disableAllRollupTriggers()` before processing to prevent rollup recalculations from compounding DML costs during mass record conversion. Both `Database.update(convertedRDs, false)` and `Database.delete(opps, false)` use partial-success DML so a single bad record does not abort the entire batch; the logger collects per-record failures that feed the enablement UI. In dry-run mode (or when any related record fails), a `Database.rollback(sp)` rolls back all changes in the batch scope so no data is persisted during validation runs."
