        "description": "Executes asynchronous operations for Enhanced Recurring Donations, including Opportunity evaluation, commitment cancellation, and name refreshes, by implementing the Queueable interface. It provides static entry points that trigger handlers and services call to defer heavy processing to a separate transaction, preventing governor limit issues during synchronous trigger execution. The source code This class is the concurrency guard for the domain: a static `alreadyEnqueuedIds` set tracks which RD IDs have already been dispatched in the current transaction, and `removeAlreadyEnqueuedRecurringDonations` filters duplicates before calling `System.enqueueJob` — preventing a race condition where multiple trigger contexts in the same transaction would each enqueue evaluation for the same RD. When the queueable job limit is reached or Gift Entry mode is active, processing falls back to synchronous `executeOppEvaluationService()` in the same transaction. The `CancelCommitmentService` inner class implements both Queueable and Database.AllowsCallouts so Elevate cancellation callouts can execute asynchronously without governor-limit conflicts."
