        "description": "Manages all aspects of installment schedule creation, visualization, and date calculation for Enhanced Recurring Donations — the backbone of the scheduling engine consumed by trigger handlers, batch jobs, and UI controllers. It builds new Recurring Donation Schedule records with amount, frequency, period, day of month, start and end dates, and manages pause periods. The service calculates next donation dates, evaluates schedule end dates, and generates visualized installment projections for the Upcoming Installments component. It supports monthly, quarterly, yearly, and custom Advanced schedules (e.g., every 3 months) with configurable Day of Month. The source code At 1,295 lines — the largest class in the domain — this service owns all installment date arithmetic, using 45 null guards and 78 lists to handle the many combinations of period type, frequency, day-of-month, and pause state. For the \"1st and 15th\" installment period it creates two schedule records per RD (one with DayOfMonth = 1, one with DayOfMonth = 15) in a single `buildNewSchedules` call. Schedule end dates are computed with `addDays(-1)` arithmetic so that consecutive schedules share no overlapping day. A savepoint/rollback pattern exists inside the service for scenarios where schedule recalculation must be transactionally atomic."
