        "description": "Evaluates and updates the Sustainer field on Contact and Account records based on their association with Enhanced Recurring Donations. The Sustainer field values are: Active (one or more Active Recurring Donations), Lapsed (one or more Lapsed but none Active), and Former (only Closed). NPSP automatically updates these values based on the Status of related Recurring Donations. This service compares current sustainer status against the actual Recurring Donation state and returns lists of Contacts and Accounts that need updates, running in both trigger and batch contexts to keep donor sustainer designations accurate. The source code The service computes Contact and Account sustainer designations (Active, Lapsed, Former) by comparing the current sustainer value against the highest-priority RD status found in the related `npe03__RecurringDonations__r` and `npe03__R00N80000002bOmREAU__r` relationship collections — the second relationship is the legacy Account-to-RD lookup noted earlier. By returning lists of records that need updates rather than performing DML itself, the service allows its callers to batch the sustainer writes alongside other record updates."
