        "description": "Enforces all business validation rules for Enhanced Recurring Donations during insert and update operations. It validates that either a Contact or Account donor reference is populated, that Amount is a positive value, that Installment Period and Frequency form a valid schedule, that Day of Month is appropriate for the selected period, and that Date Established and Effective Date meet constraints. For Fixed-Length types, it validates the Number of Planned Installments. It also validates Elevate-specific constraints when an Elevate Commitment ID is present, blocking changes that the external payment platform cannot accommodate. This service is called by the trigger handler and entry form controller to prevent invalid data from being saved. The source code At 736 lines with 28 validation call sites and 28 custom labels, this service is the most comprehensive validation layer in the domain, covering Elevate-specific constraints as a second validation pass on top of the standard checks. For Elevate records, it blocks: reactivation after close, changes to Contact/Organization/PaymentMethod/Campaign/Amount/DayOfMonth/InstallmentPeriod on a closed record, future-dated EndDates, Fixed-Length type, and status changes. Four SOQL queries are used to retrieve related Opportunities (for EndDate validation against the last Closed Won Opp) and account records (for donor validation)."
