        "description": "Custom Settings object that lets administrators specify which Relationship fields should not be automatically synchronized to the reciprocal record. When the Enable Custom Field Sync option is active in NPSP Settings, any change to a Relationship field is mirrored to the reciprocal record. Fields listed in this exclusion setting are skipped during that sync, preserving different values on each side of the relationship pair. This is configured in NPSP Settings under Relationships > General Relationships Settings > Fields to Exclude from Sync. Common uses include excluding description or custom fields that intentionally hold different information for each Contact — for instance, a note that is relevant from one person's perspective but not the other's.",
