        "description": "TDTM trigger on Relationship records that fires on all seven standard record change events. It serves as the single automation entry point for all relationship operations, delegating to the TDTM dispatcher which routes processing to the primary relationship handler. That handler performs reciprocal record creation on insert, field synchronization on update (including Status and custom field propagation), and cascading deletion on delete. The before-context events allow validation and field defaulting before records are committed to the database."
